author: sussman
msg: Fix mod_dav_svn segfault: stop trying to generate VCC liveprops which
require a defined fs_root/fs_path.  This segfault was only stimulated
by foreign DeltaV requests;  the svn client always asks for a single
specific VCC prop, whereas a foreign client might ask for *all* props.
[ For now, a VCC only has the following props defined:
{DAV:checked-in, DAV:auto-version, svn:repository-uuid}.  Someday
(for interop), it needs to support *all* standard VCR props, as well
as the special DAV:baseline-controlled-collection prop. ]
* mod_dav_svn/liveprops.c (dav_svn_insert_prop): look for VCC private
kind, and add explicit bails in the cases for 'etag',
'creationdate', 'creator-displayname', and 'version-name'.
